title: For Sale:  Marlin 25MN 22WMR/22MAG
postcontent: Marlin model 25MN in 22wmr, it is a JM stamped rifle. When I received this rifle it was in poor condition, the stock was horrible, and the entire action and barrel were canted, and not level. I test shot it at 50yards and could not get anything better then a 3" group. That's when I tore the entire gun down, sanded the barrel channel down, bedded the barrel pillar bolt, put in a bedding block under the barrel around the pillar constructed of professional grade autobody Duraglass, after all that I noticed the rear action would still not seat properly on the stock. That's when I decided to add a rear action screw. I welded a 7/16 nut to the rear action, bored the stock, and now everything sits level, and this gun will shoot same hole at 50yds. All the bottom metal has been painted high gloss black enamel, the stock was completely redone in a beautiful cognac finish, and cleared with high gloss high build polyurethane clear. I then polished the bolt with 200grit-2000grit sand paper to add a custom look, and the bolt cycles smooth as silk now. The barrel has some wear marks but doeant have rust, the mags do however have some surface rust, i was going to sand them down and repaint them but have heard horror stories of paint build on and in the magazine springs. The rifle comes with 2 magazines $200 obo or trades welcome!  please no muzzleloaders  or bows! Send me a message with any questions or offers!
